1
00:01:08,300 --> 00:01:10,800
"Blue Lips"

2
00:01:11,200 --> 00:01:13,700
(Episode 3)

3
00:01:22,980 --> 00:01:24,079
What are you trying to do?

4
00:01:25,679 --> 00:01:27,199
Is this the solution you talked about?

5
00:01:27,380 --> 00:01:28,460
To put it simply,

6
00:01:28,599 --> 00:01:30,280
men and women are the same.

7
00:01:30,579 --> 00:01:31,579
In your situation,

8
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:33,199
it can be resolved by ejaculating.

9
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:34,400
Stop, stop, stop.

10
00:01:34,579 --> 00:01:35,579
Don't say another word.

11
00:01:36,679 --> 00:01:38,479
I don't understand
any of this medical stuff.

12
00:01:38,599 --> 00:01:39,599
Just tell me

13
00:01:39,940 --> 00:01:41,059
what I need to do.

14
00:01:42,199 --> 00:01:43,539
Simply put,

15
00:01:44,880 --> 00:01:45,880
that method.

16
00:01:47,900 --> 00:01:49,059
I've tried it,

17
00:01:49,420 --> 00:01:50,579
but I couldn't get it out.

18
00:01:51,019 --> 00:01:52,396
That's because your technique is bad.

19
00:01:52,420 --> 00:01:53,000
Leave it to me.

20
00:01:53,139 --> 00:01:54,139
You...

21
00:01:55,079 --> 00:01:56,079
Wait.

22
00:01:56,480 --> 00:01:57,600
Why do you have an umbrella?

23
00:02:00,780 --> 00:02:02,559
It's a preventive measure.

24
00:02:03,019 --> 00:02:04,316
Just in case you get it on me later.

25
00:02:04,340 --> 00:02:04,860
Otherwise,

26
00:02:05,119 --> 00:02:06,280
I'll be scarred for life.

27
00:02:08,340 --> 00:02:09,380
You're going too far!

28
00:02:09,900 --> 00:02:10,900
Young man,

29
00:02:11,260 --> 00:02:14,099
you know nothing about the
wonders of the human body.

30
00:02:14,579 --> 00:02:15,239
In a moment,

31
00:02:15,539 --> 00:02:18,460
you'll realize how
brilliant my decision was.

32
00:02:20,340 --> 00:02:21,340
Come on.

33
00:02:37,539 --> 00:02:38,539
Relax, relax, relax.

34
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,739
It's my first time doing this, too.

35
00:02:46,340 --> 00:02:47,340
Now!

36
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:00,400
So?

37
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:01,840
Much better, right?

38
00:03:03,300 --> 00:03:04,300
I think...

39
00:03:05,340 --> 00:03:06,340
it's a bit better.

40
00:03:07,559 --> 00:03:08,179
That's good.

41
00:03:08,579 --> 00:03:10,019
We'll continue in a bit.

42
00:03:11,519 --> 00:03:12,880
We have to continue?

43
00:03:13,619 --> 00:03:14,619
Of course.

44
00:03:14,780 --> 00:03:16,538
Even if the drug doesn't last three days,

45
00:03:16,539 --> 00:03:18,340
it'll still be effective
for over ten hours.

46
00:03:18,780 --> 00:03:19,460
But since you

47
00:03:19,699 --> 00:03:20,719
just finished one round,

48
00:03:20,739 --> 00:03:21,859
drink some water to ease it.

49
00:03:21,940 --> 00:03:23,220
We'll go for round two in a bit.

50
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:27,280
Right now,

51
00:03:27,739 --> 00:03:29,339
just hearing the word "water" scares me.

52
00:03:30,860 --> 00:03:31,320
Alright then.

53
00:03:31,860 --> 00:03:32,519
Take a break.

54
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:33,800
I'll be back in a moment.

55
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:36,840
Wait.

56
00:03:39,679 --> 00:03:40,219
I...

57
00:03:40,679 --> 00:03:42,719
I think it's starting again.

58
00:03:51,380 --> 00:03:52,219
No way.

59
00:03:52,219 --> 00:03:53,219
Are you...

60
00:03:53,300 --> 00:03:55,739
Should I say you're too young,

61
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:57,940
or is this drug just too strong?

62
00:03:58,400 --> 00:03:59,400
This...

63
00:04:00,139 --> 00:04:01,139
Come on.

64
00:04:06,780 --> 00:04:07,780
How does it feel?

65
00:04:08,960 --> 00:04:09,179
Why...

66
00:04:09,380 --> 00:04:10,179
Why are you asking that?

67
00:04:10,179 --> 00:04:11,179
What's happening?

68
00:04:11,300 --> 00:04:12,540
It's getting hotter and hotter.

69
00:04:19,380 --> 00:04:20,380
I'm cold.

70
00:04:20,719 --> 00:04:21,999
Then I'll take off the raincoat.

71
00:04:22,059 --> 00:04:23,840
He isn't wearing gloves.

72
00:04:34,639 --> 00:04:35,719
Are you feeling any better?

73
00:04:37,340 --> 00:04:38,440
Once I recover,

74
00:04:39,380 --> 00:04:40,980
I'm going to beat you

75
00:04:41,699 --> 00:04:42,880
to a pulp.

76
00:04:44,179 --> 00:04:45,819
We'll talk about that when you're better.

77
00:04:46,780 --> 00:04:47,780
By the way,

78
00:04:49,579 --> 00:04:51,079
what was your name again?

79
00:04:52,380 --> 00:04:53,380
My name is Teng Mo.

80
00:04:59,159 --> 00:05:00,159
Teng Mo.

81
00:05:03,199 --> 00:05:04,199
I...

82
00:05:04,699 --> 00:05:05,699
I'm so scared.

83
00:05:07,420 --> 00:05:08,420
Tell me,

84
00:05:10,960 --> 00:05:12,579
am I going to die?

85
00:05:14,940 --> 00:05:16,519
Nobody dies from this.

86
00:05:22,760 --> 00:05:23,760
Alright.

87
00:05:24,260 --> 00:05:25,260
Why don't you

88
00:05:25,420 --> 00:05:26,960
get up and take a shower?

89
00:05:29,099 --> 00:05:30,139
I have no strength left.

90
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:32,920
Teng Mo,

91
00:05:35,260 --> 00:05:36,639
am I ruined?

92
00:05:38,019 --> 00:05:39,019
Why would you say that?

93
00:05:41,820 --> 00:05:42,920
It seems like

94
00:05:43,900 --> 00:05:45,280
it won't go down.

95
00:05:49,519 --> 00:05:50,519
It hurts.

96
00:05:51,800 --> 00:05:53,940
Repeated friction on
human skin causes pain.

97
00:05:57,119 --> 00:05:58,159
Change your clothes first.

98
00:06:00,340 --> 00:06:02,440
Is there really no other way?

99
00:06:03,719 --> 00:06:04,719
Do you trust me?

100
00:06:07,300 --> 00:06:08,300
Teng Mo,

101
00:06:09,840 --> 00:06:10,840
help me.

102
00:06:35,820 --> 00:06:36,820
Is it warm?

103
00:06:47,219 --> 00:06:48,400
Can you make it quick later?

104
00:06:49,079 --> 00:06:50,079
I still need to go home.

105
00:06:53,139 --> 00:06:54,539
Then why don't you close your eyes?

106
00:06:56,039 --> 00:06:57,039
Why?

107
00:06:58,559 --> 00:06:59,800
Because if you can't see me,

108
00:07:00,400 --> 00:07:01,400
you won't be annoyed.

109
00:07:03,679 --> 00:07:04,679
I'm not...

110
00:07:05,239 --> 00:07:06,559
I don't dislike you that much.

111
00:07:21,099 --> 00:07:22,099
Have you ever tried

112
00:07:22,460 --> 00:07:23,480
kissing a man?

113
00:07:45,639 --> 00:07:46,639
Did you feel anything?

114
00:07:49,880 --> 00:07:50,880
It was too brief.

115
00:07:51,579 --> 00:07:52,579
I don't know.

116
00:09:57,239 --> 00:09:58,239
Again?

117
00:10:24,699 --> 00:10:26,260
These sleeves are so warm.

118
00:10:27,420 --> 00:10:28,779
Can I draw close to
you for a moment?

119
00:11:38,579 --> 00:11:39,819
I wanted to prank someone else,

120
00:11:40,039 --> 00:11:41,220
but ended up pranking myself.

121
00:11:43,659 --> 00:11:44,659
You little wolf.

122
00:11:44,880 --> 00:11:45,960
Impressive.

123
00:11:49,420 --> 00:11:50,239
Didn't I decide

124
00:11:50,240 --> 00:11:51,400
not to drag others into this?

125
00:11:52,380 --> 00:11:53,380
Have you used it?

126
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:55,000
No.

127
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:57,656
If you've never used it, why
the hell did you give it to me?

128
00:11:57,680 --> 00:11:58,180
Fine.

129
00:11:58,579 --> 00:12:00,100
We'll go to the hospital in a bit.

130
00:12:07,039 --> 00:12:08,079
It doesn't matter anymore.

131
00:12:08,439 --> 00:12:09,439
It's over.

132
00:12:16,180 --> 00:12:17,180
Feel free to look around.

133
00:12:28,039 --> 00:12:29,039
Do you want this one?

134
00:12:29,399 --> 00:12:30,659
Which of these is better?

135
00:12:30,739 --> 00:12:31,119
This one.

136
00:12:31,359 --> 00:12:31,899
It's our best seller.

137
00:12:31,899 --> 00:12:32,500
How much is this?

138
00:12:32,840 --> 00:12:33,619
Thirty. Scan the code.

139
00:12:33,620 --> 00:12:34,640
Thirty. Alright.

140
00:12:48,979 --> 00:12:49,979
Take this.

141
00:12:50,199 --> 00:12:50,739
This month

142
00:12:50,920 --> 00:12:51,500
and next month,

143
00:12:51,880 --> 00:12:53,360
I won't request songs that annoy you.

144
00:13:55,239 --> 00:13:56,239
How was yesterday?

145
00:13:56,880 --> 00:13:57,880
It was alright.

146
00:14:02,899 --> 00:14:03,619
He sang really well.

147
00:14:03,859 --> 00:14:05,179
Would you like to request a song?

148
00:14:15,859 --> 00:14:16,439
Wu Shixian,

149
00:14:16,520 --> 00:14:17,520
someone requested a song.

150
00:14:58,420 --> 00:14:59,899
Why buy Vandacon if you're healthy?

151
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:02,059
If you don't want to host at Blue Moon,

152
00:15:02,060 --> 00:15:03,960
why don't you consider finding another job?

153
00:15:16,439 --> 00:15:17,439
Xiao Wu,

154
00:15:18,779 --> 00:15:19,779
Xiao Wu.

155
00:15:23,640 --> 00:15:24,640
Your guitar.

156
00:16:24,279 --> 00:16:25,279
Here.

157
00:16:25,859 --> 00:16:26,859
Buying medicine?

158
00:16:35,439 --> 00:16:36,439
Vandacon again?

159
00:16:40,819 --> 00:16:42,699
Have you thought about
trying another medicine?

160
00:16:48,819 --> 00:16:49,819
Fine.

161
00:16:50,100 --> 00:16:50,579
Never mind.

162
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:52,000
The usual, then.

163
00:16:52,060 --> 00:16:53,060
Four hundred and fifty.

164
00:17:10,180 --> 00:17:11,180
Lately,

165
00:17:15,260 --> 00:17:16,900
why haven't you been coming to Blue Moon?

166
00:17:18,859 --> 00:17:19,859
Didn't I promise you?

167
00:17:21,819 --> 00:17:22,859
If you took that medicine,

168
00:17:23,340 --> 00:17:25,279
I wouldn't request songs
that annoy you for months.

169
00:17:28,319 --> 00:17:29,599
Even if you don't request songs,

170
00:17:29,680 --> 00:17:30,920
you can still come for a drink.

171
00:17:33,760 --> 00:17:35,600
I don't usually drink much.

172
00:17:38,779 --> 00:17:39,180
Well,

173
00:17:39,539 --> 00:17:40,979
you could request some normal songs.

174
00:17:47,159 --> 00:17:48,560
I thought you didn't want me there.

175
00:17:50,720 --> 00:17:51,819
Blue Moon isn't my house.

176
00:17:58,680 --> 00:18:00,000
So, you do want me to go?

177
00:18:06,859 --> 00:18:07,560
Suit yourself.

178
00:18:07,840 --> 00:18:08,840
Who cares?

179
00:18:26,680 --> 00:18:27,680
A'Heng.

180
00:18:28,100 --> 00:18:29,100
Brother Mo!

181
00:18:29,659 --> 00:18:31,015
It's been a while since
you visited Blue Moon.

182
00:18:31,039 --> 00:18:32,039
Whiskey as usual?

183
00:18:32,680 --> 00:18:33,039
Actually, no.

184
00:18:33,159 --> 00:18:34,760
I'll have a Long Island Iced Tea today.

185
00:18:34,880 --> 00:18:35,880
Sure.

186
00:18:51,619 --> 00:18:52,619
Here you go.

187
00:18:56,800 --> 00:18:57,800
Iced tea.

188
00:19:01,060 --> 00:19:02,060
Not bad.

189
00:19:02,279 --> 00:19:03,279
Request a song?

190
00:19:05,039 --> 00:19:06,239
Someone already requested one.

191
00:19:33,460 --> 00:19:34,660
This song is really beautiful.

192
00:19:36,060 --> 00:19:37,060
What's it called?

193
00:19:37,380 --> 00:19:38,760
Let me tell you a secret.

194
00:19:40,479 --> 00:19:41,479
What is it?

195
00:19:43,560 --> 00:19:45,720
The song is called "Let
Me Tell You a Secret."

